channel.desc: Join the crew of the Straw Hat Pirates and set a course for anime adventure with One Piece. The global phenomenon is now a 24/7 channel on Pluto TV.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.desc: Nami’s adopted sister, Nojiko arrives to fill in some details about the skilled mapmaker’s younger days.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Survive! Mother Bellemere and Nami's Bond!
programme.desc: Nojiko continues the story of Nami’s younger days. Back in the present, Nami gets agonizingly close to a long time goal, but betrayal looms on the horizon.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Luffy Rises! Result of the Broken Promise!
programme.desc: Nezumi comes to confiscate Nami’s treasure, but who’s he working for? More importantly, who’s Nami working for, and what’s she gonna do with her booty?

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Luffy in Big Trouble! Fishmen vs. the Luffy Pirates!
programme.desc: The Straw Hats’ faith in Nami is restored, and now it’s time for a battle royal! Luffy and the gang are determined to make Arlong pay for mistreating their friend.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Luffy Submerged! Zoro vs. Hatchan the Octopus!
programme.desc: The Straw Hats and Arlong’s fishermen are locked in a swashbuckling slugfest, but things take a bad turn when Luffy gets trapped beneath the waves.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Proud Warriors! Sanji and Usopp's Fierce Battles!
programme.desc: While his friends work to free the captain of the Straw Hats, cowardly Usopp finds himself in a position to shed his yellow streak and make his father proud.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Luffy at Full Power! Nami's Determination and the Straw Hat!
programme.desc: Nami must decide between letting Arlong maintain his hold over her, or joining the Straw Hats and leading the oppressed villagers against the tyrant Fishman.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Explosion! Fishman Arlong's Fierce Assault From the Sea!
programme.desc: Arlong better watch his back-fins, because Captain Luffy knows about all the horrible things he did to Nami – and it makes his blood boil.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: End of the Fishman Empire! Nami's My Friend!
programme.desc: Something about Nami’s former prison gives Luffy an added burst of strength. He’s so moved by her terrible past that he vows to destroy all of Arlong Park!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Setting Out with a Smile! Farewell, Hometown Cocoyashi Village!
programme.desc: After a grueling fight, Luffy defeats Arlong and succeeds in destroying his headquarters. The merry marauders enjoy the fruits of victory while Nami makes peace with her turbulent past.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Bounty! Straw Hat Luffy Becomes Known to the World!
programme.desc: Finally, the day has arrived where Luffy’s face is on an authentic wanted poster! Now there are enemies in hot pursuit as the crew makes waves for Logue Town – the final resting place of Gold Roger!

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Chase Straw Hat! Little Buggy's Big Adventure!
programme.desc: Buggy gets marooned on an island inhabited by unusual creatures and tangles with the island’s caretaker, Gaimon. If he is to finally destroy Luffy, Buggy must cast his lot with a mysterious woman.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: The Wait is Over! The Return of Captain Buggy!
programme.desc: The Buggy Pirates fight each other for the right to take their lost captain’s place. While they’re busy beating each other’s brains out, a cannibalistic tribe makes plans to have something special for dinner.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: The Town of the Beginning and the End! Landfall at Logue Town!
programme.desc: The Straw Hats arrive at Logue Town, and each crewmember embarks upon a mission of a more personal nature. While his crew shops, Luffy goes in search of sacred ground.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Kitetsu III and Yubashiri! Zoro's New Swords and the Woman Sergeant Major!
programme.desc: Luffy has a run-in with Captain Smoker, and his failure to keep a low profile helps Buggy draw a bead on him. Elsewhere, Zoro takes a chance that his skill can overcome a dangerous curse.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Usopp vs. Daddy the Parent! Showdown at High!
programme.desc: Usopp finds an amazing pair of sharpshooter’s goggles, but they lead to a run-in with Daddy the Parent – the greatest gunslinger ever! Now, the Straw Hat marksman is headed for the deadliest of all duels.

programme.title: One Piece
programme.sub-title: Fiery Cooking Battle? Sanji vs. the Beautiful Chef!
programme.desc: A cooking competition with the fiery chef Carmen rekindles Sanji’s dreams of the legendary All Blue.

channel.desc: The Doctor will see you now. Dr. Mehmet Oz is bringing his Emmy-award winning series to Pluto TV, with talk about health, fitness, nutrition, and being your best self.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.sub-title: 99 Food Hacks You Can't Live Without
programme.desc: We brought the biggest names in food together to find amazing ways to save you time, money, and calories. From quick morning meals to no-fry fried chicken for dinner. Fun, fast, foolproof fixes for every day of the year.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.sub-title: Elizabeth Smart – “Whatever It Took To Survive”
programme.desc: KIDNAPPING VICTIM ELIZABETH SMART reveals how she found strength during her captivity and why gratitude paved the way for her newfound happiness. How anyone struggling with life’s toughest challenges can be inspired by her story.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.sub-title: True Crime Tuesdays: Fetal Abductions: Babies Stolen From The Womb
programme.desc: What would drive someone to abduct a child still in the mother's womb and viciously attempt to carve the fetus out of her belly? Today, one survivor tells her horrifying story. Then, meet a young man who survived being ripped from his mother's womb.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.sub-title: True Crime Tuesdays: Sexual Assault During Massages
programme.desc: We go undercover in backroom spas and massage parlors to see what's really going on. Meet women who say they went in for a relaxing break and came out shaken to their core. Then, women speak out about the first time they were sexually assaulted.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.sub-title: True Crime Tuesdays: The New Internet Drug Craze
programme.desc: It's ten times more potent than cocaine and it makes people think they've got super-human strength and act completely out of control. We investigate the designer drugs popping up all over the country and the high-tech way to protect your loved ones.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.sub-title: Did You Live A Past Life? The Science Behind Regression Therapy
programme.desc: A ground-breaking experiment uncovers what's really going in our brain during a past life regression. Is there real science behind spirit? Wayne Brady reveals the painful health secret he’s kept hidden for years and what motivated him to get help.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.sub-title: Theresa Caputo Sets The Record Straight
programme.desc: Long Island Medium Theresa Caputo captivates audiences with her self-proclaimed gift of communicating with the dead. But there are some critics who question her legitimacy. See what a world traveler has learned from the people who live to be 100.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.sub-title: Back From The Dead Stories: The Man Who Said He Went To Hell
programme.desc: You'll hear from a man who says his experience in hell was so bone chilling - it changed his life forever. Psychic mediums Char Margolis and John Edward come together to share exactly how their powers work and how you can tap into your intuition.

programme.title: The Dr. Oz Show
programme.desc: A cover model for over 40 years, at age 61, Christie Brinkley reveals her anti-aging secrets. From what she eats throughout her day to the daily skin ritual she swears by. Plus, how to reprogram your taste buds to crave healthy food.

channel.desc: Take a trip across the pond with the one channel bringing you the very best in British home remodeling and garden renovation, all day, every day.

programme.title: Building Dream Homes

programme.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build

programme.title: Kirstie Allsopp's Home Style

programme.title: Kirstie's Vintage Home
programme.desc: Cheshire couple Iman and Heather dream of turning their sitting room into a twenties inspired space, and they'd like a vintage nursery to boot. A new house means a blank canvas and, therefore, a perfect space for Kirstie to work her magic.

programme.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build
programme.desc: The team help adapt a home for a hospital worker injured in a motorcycle accident.

programme.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build
programme.desc: The team travels to Chesterfield to help Lisa and Richard Watson and their young family.

programme.title: Gok's Fill Your House for Free
programme.desc: Gok and his team face a tough test when Sara and Ryan come to the shop. Despite the arrival of a baby boy seven months ago, they've worked like dogs to get their Edwardian semi renovated and need a bit of help to get it finally finished.

channel.desc: Step into the kitchen with some of the finest chefs in the British Isles, including Nigella Lawson, Jamie Oliver, Rachel Allen, and more, where something wonderful is always cooking.

programme.title: Rachel Khoo's Kitchen Notebook: Melbourne
programme.desc: Rachel uncovers one of Melbourne's hidden secret day trips when she explores the Dandenong region. She meets up with passionate Argentinian Chef Mauro, from The Independent restaurant, who she will cook alongside using locally caught golden trout.

programme.title: Raymond Blanc's Kitchen Secrets
programme.desc: Chef Raymond Blanc combines the universally popular ingredients egg and cheese to make a classic omelette. He also visits a fromagerie.

programme.title: Rachel Khoo's Cosmopolitan Cook
programme.desc: Rachel takes things easy as she hops on a boat to the tranquil Princes' Islands.

programme.title: Hemsley + Hemsley Healthy and Delicious
programme.desc: When throwing a party it's easy for nutrition to take a back seat. Not so for foodie sisters Jasmine and Melissa Hemsley who have come up with a menu that will impress your guests as well as keep them eating healthily.

programme.title: Mary Berry at Home
programme.desc: Mary prepares a feast for four hundred garden party guests. Dishes include a collette of plaice, hazelnut meringue torte, cream teas, and chocolate cake.

programme.title: The Naked Chef
programme.desc: Jamie and fiancee Jules entertain their respective future in-laws. Among the dishes prepared in this episode is linguine with olive oil, salmon fillet wrapped in prosciutto with herby lentils, and fruit sorbet.

programme.title: Ainsley's Gourmet Express
programme.desc: Inspired by Japan's fabulous food and the Far East, Ainsley demonstrates how to make perfect sushi and tempura and prawns and peanuts pan-fried upon noodles Thai-style yellow pork curry, and Top chef Clive Fretwell demonstrates the art of sushi-making.

programme.title: The Hairy Bikers' Mississippi Adventure
programme.desc: The duo takes the road to Nashville, Tennessee, where they learn about the roots of country music, cook biscuits and gravy, and visit the Grand Ole Opry stage.

programme.title: The Hairy Bikers' Mississippi Adventure
programme.desc: Dave and Si continue their journey as they head to New Orleans, where they meet blues musician Little Freddie King and get to grips with some of the best local food, providing their own twist to a southern classic - po'boy, a traditional sandwich.

programme.title: Raymond Blanc's Kitchen Secrets
programme.desc: Raymond creates a celebration of the season: a winter vegetable salad featuring pumpkin, beets, wild mushrooms, and a red wine reduction. Raymond tries his hand at cutting watercress in Britain's watercress capital, Arlesford in Hampshire.

programme.title: Hemsley + Hemsley Healthy and Delicious
programme.desc: Jasmine and Melissa Hemsley create nutrient-rich dishes that will warm you up on a cold day. From buckwheat porridge with coconut to their signature bone broth, they offer nutritionally high alternatives to the carbs we're often drawn to when it's chilly.

programme.title: The Naked Chef
programme.desc: Jamie goes go-karting with his friends and replenishes his larder. He cooks blackened sweet aubergine, stuffed baby-bell chilli peppers, carpaccio of beef, and a crunchy Thai noodle salad.
